# Force binary handling for checked-in binary fixtures/assets, regardless of
# git's own NUL-byte heuristic. Without this, `core.autocrlf` on Windows
# checkouts can silently rewrite LF -> CRLF in a binary file that git
# mis-detects as text (most likely for small, hand-crafted fixtures with no
# NUL byte in their first ~8000 bytes) — corrupting exact byte offsets that
# formats like PDF depend on (xref tables). This was the root cause of a
# Windows-only PdfTextExtractor test failure on the minimal, hand-constructed
# `zero_pages_synthetic.pdf` fixture (packages/kmdb_extractor_pdf/test/fixtures/):
# every other PDF fixture is large/complex enough to contain a NUL byte early
# on and was therefore auto-detected as binary regardless.
*.pdf binary
*.png binary
*.ico binary
